Argentine Stocks: Banco Hipotecario, Grupo Galicia and Ledesma

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-02-25T20:57:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/argentine-stocks-banco-hipotecario-grupo-galicia-and-ledesma.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 3:00 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index rose 1.6 percent to 3,435.44.    Grupo Financiero Galicia SA  (GGAL AF), Argentina’s largest
consumer lender, rose 2.2 percent to 6.04 pesos, the largest
increase in more than a week. Argentine banks rose today as the
price of sovereign bonds increased, signaling higher values for
banks’ fixed-income holdings.  Banco Hipotecario SA  (BHIP AF)
climbed 4.5 percent to 2.78 pesos,  BBVA Banco Frances SA  (FRAN
AF) rose 2.6 percent to 16 pesos and Banco Macro SA (BMA AF)
gained 3.2 percent to 17.65 pesos.  Ledesma SAAI (LEDE AF) rose 5.2 percent to 9.15 pesos, the
largest increase in seven weeks. The Argentine sugar producer
rose as sugar prices advanced in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
